<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-11T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-11T23:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/596</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Price</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-11T23:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1917, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received midnight.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Supplementing my May 11, 3 p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d380fn1">Not
                                    printed.</note> Salvador’s reply same as Honduras’s. Nicaragua
                                simply applauds the initiative. Guatemala [accepts?] in principle
                                and states that it will appoint a delegate as soon as details are
                                known.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWJ1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>